title.narrative: OUTPUT 3.3: EDUCATION ENABLING ENVIRONMENT

description.narrative: Capacity of education sector at subnational and national levels is strengthened to legislate, plan, coordinate and budget the provision of equitable and inclusive education opportunities, which contributes to Access To Quality Learning Opportunities, Access To Quality Learning Opportunities (Covid), Cross-Sectoral - Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral - Planning And Programme Reviews, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Partnerships And Engagement: Public And Private, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2021, more children have access to early stimulation and quality basic education and learning in inclusive and safe school environments.

description.narrative: In 2021, UNICEF remained the Coordinating Agent of three Global Partnership of Education (GPE) grants, which has contributed to the safe school reopening of the public schools in Basic Education and impacting16,475schools and5,585,417students.; UNICEF also supported the Ministry of Education on EMIS functionality review that provided recommendations on the priority areas of improvements.
